# Android eInk / Low-Refresh-Rate Display Constraints

> **openclaw-ui** is a web app; this rule applies only if you add Android Kotlin/XML sources. Skip otherwise.

eInk screens refresh slowly and produce visible ghosting artefacts when animations or transitions are used. **Never use any animation or transition** in code targeting eInk or low-refresh-rate displays.

## Prohibited APIs

Do not use any of the following:

- `animate()` (View property animator)
- `ObjectAnimator`
- `ValueAnimator`
- `ViewPropertyAnimator`
- `Transition` / `TransitionManager`
- `MotionLayout`
- `animateLayoutChanges="true"` in XML layouts
- Non-zero `windowAnimationStyle` in themes

## Dialog Animations

Always explicitly disable dialog window animations:

```kotlin
dialog.window?.setWindowAnimations(0)
```

## Activity Transitions

Always cancel activity enter/exit transitions immediately after starting an activity:

```kotlin
startActivity(intent)
overridePendingTransition(0, 0)
```

## Layout Changes

In any XML layout file, ensure `animateLayoutChanges` is not set to `true`:

```xml
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<LinearLayout android:animateLayoutChanges="true" ... />

<!-- ✅ GOOD — omit the attribute entirely or set to false -->
<LinearLayout ... />
```
